## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Dense, solid, unyielding, direct.
    - Feedback: Very clear and crisp. You know exactly where on the racket the ball made contact.
    - Hold vs. Release: Short hold time unless you strike the ball with massive force, after which it releases like a cannon.
    - Dwell Time: Visually and mechanically short compared to standard T05; requires the player to artificially create dwell through stroke mechanics.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a sharp, loud crack on high impact, replacing the metallic tink of softer ESN/Spring Sponge rubbers.

