## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC). The classic professional pairing. Delivers maximum direct power but requires perfect technique.
    - Inner Carbon: (e.g., Innerforce Layer ALC). An excellent choice for advanced players wanting to add a fraction more dwell time to tame the rubber's hardness.
    - All-Wood: (e.g., Korbel, Clipper). Good for taming the speed and adding natural arc, though high-level players might find it lacks top-end power.
    - Mismatch Cases: Extremely stiff carbon blades (e.g., Tamca 5000) will make the setup feel like a frying pan. Very soft, flexible blades may create a disjointed, vibrating feel.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: The primary and highly recommended use case. Suits the longer, more powerful biomechanics of the forehand stroke perfectly.
    - Backhand: Only recommended for top-tier professionals or players with exceptionally explosive backhand strokes. For 95% of players, it is too hard for the backhand.

